According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Hair Dye Market was valued at USD 36.6 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 39.1 billion in 2026 to approximately USD 66 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 6.7% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing robust growth as consumers increasingly prioritize personal grooming, self-expression, and appearance enhancement across all age groups. Rising disposable incomes, expanding fashion consciousness, and the growing popularity of at-home hair coloring products are driving sustained demand worldwide. At the same time, manufacturers are responding to increasing consumer preference for safer, ammonia-free, vegan, and plant-based formulations by investing heavily in product innovation and sustainable ingredients.
